videos.description: Tennessee's Grant Williams puts down a huge, one-hand slam over a Lipscomb defender.
videos.headline: Williams throws down monster dunk

videos.description: Tennessee's Kyle Alexander leaps for a big block and Lamonte Turner finishes strong on the other end.
videos.headline: Alexander's block leads to a Turner fast-break slam

videos.description: Lamonte Turner sinks the mid-range shot right before the end of the first half to put Tennessee up 40-27 over Lipscomb.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Turner drains the jumper at the buzzer

videos.description: Tennessee's Kyle Alexander denies the fast break with a big block.
videos.headline: Alexander stuffs the layup attempt

videos.description: Lipscomb's Garrison Matthews spins in midair and still finishes off the glass despite the foul.
videos.headline: Matthews makes a sweet spinning layup

videos.description: In its first game as a ranked team since December 2010, No. 24 Tennessee defeats Lipscomb 81-71 behind Grant Williams' 19 points.
videos.headline: Volunteers earn 10-point victory
